<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Size_dividers">Size divider=
s</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DClothing_s=
izes&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D28" title=3D"Edit section: Size divide=
rs"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></s=
pan></div>
<p>Size dividers are used by clothing stores to help customers find the rig=
ht size.  Like <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Index_card" title=
=3D"Index card">index cards</a>, they are found on racks between sizes.  Th=
ere are three basic types: the rectangular, round and the king size. Among =
the stores that use them are <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marsh=
alls" title=3D"Marshalls">Marshalls</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/TJ_Maxx" title=3D"TJ Maxx">TJ Maxx</a>.
</p>
